# Story 1.3: Create Seed Data Generator

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 1 - Project Foundation & Infrastructure
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-003

## User Story
As a **developer**,
I want **realistic seed data for demos**,
So that **the system demonstrates with believable railway data**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | 4-5 fleets with realistic names | PASS |
| AC2 | 12-15 depots with Portuguese cities | PASS |
| AC3 | 100-120 trains with varied mileage | PASS |
| AC4 | 200-300 daily services | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Files Created
- `apps/api/src/db/seed.ts` - Seed data generator

### Data Generated
- **Fleets:** Metro Series 2200, Metro Series 2400, Intercity Series 3400, Regional Series 4500
- **Depots:** 12 depots in Portuguese cities (Lisboa, Porto, Coimbra, Braga, Faro, etc.)
- **Trains:** 100 trains with realistic km distribution (±30% variance from fleet average)
- **Services:** 250 daily services connecting depot pairs

### Technical Decisions
- Gaussian distribution for km variance to create realistic outliers
- Haversine-based distances for service routes
- Maintenance schedules distributed across depot capacities

## Dev Notes
Seed data creates a believable demo scenario with:
- Over-running and under-running trains visible in balancing view
- Maintenance alerts for trains approaching thresholds
- Realistic route patterns between depots

